    • Method Detail

      • fillArray

        public static java.lang.String[] fillArray(java.util.Scanner fin,
                                           int total,
                                           int linesPer)
        This method creates an array of Strings with the total number of elements represented by total. Example if total is 3 then we have an array of 3 elements. Each element in the array will be a single string, meaning that if linesPer is greater than 1, then the total number in lines per will be concatenated together as a single String with each substring separated by a space. For example if the file contains
        stu
        steiner
        red
        The String that would be placed into the array would be stu steiner red as a single String
        Parameters:
        fin - Representing the Scanner object to an open file
        total - Representing the total number of elements in the array
        linesPer - Representing how many lines to concatenate into a single String
        Returns:
        String [] Representing an array filled with Strings
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if fin is null or total is less than 1 or lines per is less than 1

      • menu

        public static int menu(java.util.Scanner kb)
        The menu method prompts the user to select from the following menu choices
        1) Sort and print the array
        2) Fill a new array
        3) Write the contents of the array to a file
        4) Quit
        The method ensures the choice is within range and the input buffer is left empty at the end of the method
        Parameters:
        kb - Representing the Scanner object to the keyboard
        Returns:
        int Representing a menu choice in range from 1 to 4 for this method
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if kb is null
